Total Vacancies:2311

Name of the post:

Various posts from :

  • General Administration Department
  • Revenue Department
  • Health and Medical Education Department
  • Cooperative Department
  • Floriculture, Gardens and Parks Department
  • Department of Law, Justice and Parliamentary Affairs
  • Department of Skill Development

Description:

The Jammu and Kashmir Services Selection Board issued a total of 2311 vacancies for the posts of Junior Mechanic Technician, Junior Electrician, Junior Laboratory Technician, and various others. The online application for these posts under JKSSB shall start from 16.04.2021. The eligible and interested candidates can apply for this online application before 12.05.2021. For further detailed information regarding educational qualifications, age limit, selection procedure, how to apply, etc. for these posts is mentioned below. For more such updates do visit theprograd.com .The ProGrad jobs.

 

Mode of application & application fee:

The interested candidates after filling the application form, it is required to pay the application fee to complete the form submission process:

  • Mode of application: Online
  • The application fee for all candidates is INR 350/-
  • For more details, you can refer to the notification. The link is given at the bottom.

Important dates:

  • The Starting date to apply online is 16.04.2021
  • The Last date to apply online is 10.06.2021

Educational qualification required:

Candidates who are interested to apply should have the following qualification from a recognized University/boards with valid marks :

  • Minimum you must have a diploma in 10th to apply for any post of Junior Mechanic Technician, Junior Electrician, Junior Laboratory Technician, and various others.
  • For detailed qualification, check the official notification given at the bottom 

Age limit criteria:

  • The minimum age required to apply is 18 Years
  • The maximum age required for SC/ST/RBA/ALC /IB/EWS/PSP is 43 Years
  • The maximum age required for Ex-serviceman is 48 Years
  • The maximum age required for the rest of the candidates is 40 Years

Pay Scale:

  • The pay scale as per 7th pay commission for the post released by General Administration Department, Revenue Department, Health and Medical Education Department, Cooperative Department, Floriculture, Gardens and Parks Department, Department of Law, Justice and Parliamentary Affairs, Department of Skill Development, varies between INR 25,000 - 1,24000/MONTH
  • Check the PDF GIVEN BELOW for the detailed pay scale of every post.

Detailed vacancies:

The vacancies in detail are given below. Check below that JKSSB issued this notification for which posts.

 

How to apply for JKSSB Recruitment 2021?

  • First, visit the official website.
  • Register yourself on the portal of JKSSB.
  • Login yourself on the portal.
  • Find the notification of Junior Mechanic Technician, Junior Electrician, Junior Laboratory Technician, and various others.
  • Fill up the complete details that are asked in the application form.
  • Upload your photo and signature with the dimensions asked in the instructions.
  • Submit the application fee
  • Finally, download the application form for future needs.
